<div id="review_172813033" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/172813033" />
    <a title="Caroline " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3236194-caroline"><img alt="Caroline " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576541068p2/3236194.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/172813033?book_show_action=true">Jun 01, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Caroline " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Caroline " href="/user/show/3236194-caroline">Caroline </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Fans of quality memoirs, those wanting to know more about international child abduction</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=reading-slump-remedies">reading-slump-remedies</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=memorable-characters">memorable-characters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=truth-stranger-than-fiction">truth-stranger-than-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=mothers-and-daughters">mothers-and-daughters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=family-drama">family-drama</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=this-gets-real">this-gets-real</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=page-turner">page-turner</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3236194-caroline?shelf=maximum-impact">maximum-impact</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer172813033" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11608885954157439562"><i>Not Without My Daughter</i> is an astounding memoir that underscores just how little power women have in Iran. It&apos;s hard to believe Betty Mahmoody and her daughter survived their ordeal, but with Mahmoody&apos;s fierce persistence, they did. It was a harrowing escape, and I was captivated during this part especially. A <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_Without_My_Daughter_(film)' rel='nofollow noopener'>movie version</a> starring Sally Field and Alfred Molina was in theaters in January 1991 and is fantastic but pales in comparison to its thrilling, emotional source material. <br/><br/>On a final note: </span>
  <span id="freeText11608885954157439562" style="display:none"><i>Not Without My Daughter</i> is an astounding memoir that underscores just how little power women have in Iran. It's hard to believe Betty Mahmoody and her daughter survived their ordeal, but with Mahmoody's fierce persistence, they did. It was a harrowing escape, and I was captivated during this part especially. A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_Without_My_Daughter_(film)" rel="nofollow noopener">movie version</a> starring Sally Field and Alfred Molina was in theaters in January 1991 and is fantastic but pales in comparison to its thrilling, emotional source material. <br /><br />On a final note: I don't know why this is, but most who have read <i>Not Without My Daughter</i> are unaware that it has a sequel: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/508893.For_the_Love_of_a_Child" title="For the Love of a Child by Betty Mahmoody" rel="nofollow noopener">For the Love of a Child</a>. It shows what happened to Betty and her daughter after they escaped to America, while also explaining the heartbreaking phenomenon of international child abduction. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11608885954157439562" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


